com.esri.mo2.map.img
Interface ImageLayer

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable, DatasetLayer, Layer, Searchable
All Known Subinterfaces:
ImageServerLayer
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseImageLayer, BaseImageServerLayer
public interface ImageLayer
extends DatasetLayer

An ImageLayer is a visual representation of a particular ImageClass. When an ImageLayer is asked to draw itself, it obtains one or more images by searching the ImageClass, then displays them all. Note that a search of an ImageLayer will not return Features or attributes, just Images. See the javadoc for ImageClass for more comments about searching for Images.

See Also:
Map, Layerset, ImageClass

Method Detail

setTransparency

public void setTransparency(double value)
Sets the transparency alpha value. This will be used to determine how transparent the image should be rendered. A value of 1.0 means completely opaque, 0.0 means completely transparent. With this property the entire image is set as transparent, when compared with Transparency color which only sets one particular color as transparent. The default is normally a value of 1.0, meaning completely opaque.

Parameters:
value - the transparency value
See Also:
setTransparentColor(java.awt.Color)

setTransparentColor

public void setTransparentColor(Color color)
Sets the transparency color. This will be used to cause just one particular color to be transparent when the image is rendered, when compared with Transparency property which sets the entire image as transparent. You can set the color to be null which means there is no transparency color (this is the default).

Parameters:
color - the transparency color
See Also:
setTransparentColor(java.awt.Color)
